le=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">Chris Pento</a><=
span>, Clear Street&#8217;s CEO and co-founder, has spent his career in ope=
rations at financial institutions, from large established investment banks =
like Merrill Lynch to startup broker dealers like Exos Financial. If anyone=
 feels the brunt of bad systems, it&#8217;s the operations people who are r=
esponsible for cleaning up their mess every day.&#160;</span></p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">I asked Chris why a big bank couldn&#8217;t just throw a bunch of=
 money at the problem. He told me they probably could build new systems, be=
fore listing off a litany of reasons they wouldn&#8217;t:&#160;</p><ul styl=
