=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">As one example of the products modern infrastructure can support,=
 Clear Street can build products on its single source of truth, real-time d=
ata that take advantage of pre-trade analytics, predictive risk modeling, a=
nd intelligence instead of reactive products that wait for the data to catc=
h up.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: =
26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Studio has a &#8220;Shocks View&#8221; that lets=
 clients see what would happen to their portfolio and margin requirements i=
f asset prices swung violently up or down. It also has built-in risk simula=
tions that let clients ask &#8220;What would happen if I put this trade on?=
&#8221; both to the existing portfolio and in the case of shocks. Currently=
, to do this, traders pick up the phone and ask their risk team what the im=
pact might be. In a field in which milliseconds can make a difference, the =
speed advantage from replacing phone calls with software can be enormous.&#=
160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 2=
6px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">As another, moving everything onto one real-time =
cloud software platform means that Clear Street can provide more bespoke ma=
rgin, lending, and financing packages that respond in real-time to clients&=
#8217; portfolios.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Because Clear Street is build=
ing API-first, third parties can build products that inherit these advantag=
es on top of its infrastructure and/or Clear Street can offer those product=
s itself.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">For now, many of those products are as=
sets. Clear Street started by offering just US equities. Then it added opti=
ons, fixed income, and swaps. Now, it&#8217;s scaling out the swaps busines=
s and building a futures business.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, =
64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>In July=
, </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/02b1fa32-db92-4493-a6bb-c=
ad53418042d?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkR=
NpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">it a=
cquired React</a><span>, the maker of cloud-native futures clearing platfor=
m BASIS, and it recently applied for Futures Commission Merchant (FCM) memb=
ership. It&#8217;s the kind of acquisition a company can make when it&#8217=
;s well-capitalized enough to be acquisitive but small and technologically =
clean enough to integrate new products smoothly.</span></p><p style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
">Then, it needs to bring those products to major markets around the globe,=
 each of which has its own regulations and its own antiquated systems with =
which to integrate. My head hurts.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, =
64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Oh, and it la=
unched an investment banking business.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, =
64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Andy Volz=
, Clear Street&#8217;s COO and Head of Prime Sales, is responsible for brin=
ging in hedge fund clients. And he said that a big part of that &#8211; of =
getting hedge funds and other institutional clients to try and trust the te=
chnology Clear Street has built in the first place &#8211; is offering them=
 the services that investment banks offer.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(=
64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">&#822=
0;These are discerning customers, and it&#8217;s hard to get them to trust =
you,&#8221; Andy said. &#8220;Clients traditionally come in in one of a few=
 ways: research, corporate access, capital introductions, balance sheet. We=
 didn&#8217;t have that stuff, and now we do.&#8221;&#160;</p><p style=3D"c=
olor: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px=
 0;">And even with all of that stuff, winning prime brokerage clients still=
 requires a sales team with the right relationships. Some know a few big cl=
ients really well, others cover 200 smaller clients. Clear Street started w=
ith that group, targeting the hedge funds that the big banks don&#8217;t fo=
cus on.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-=
height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">With Studio, a self-serve product, they =
can open up the top-of-funnel even further to capture the long-tail of the =
roughly 6,000-8,000 hedge funds in their addressable market.&#160;</p><p st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: =
0 0 20px 0;">Software, services, and sales. Winning a foothold in prime bro=
kerage requires all three. And from that foothold, Clear Street can expand =
its share of wallet as it adds new products in new geographies that those s=
ame clients, and new ones, want to use.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64,=
 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Eventual=
ly, the goal is to serve all types of clients &#8211; from the day-trader t=
o the largest multi-strategy hedge funds like Alpine &#8211; across all of =
their needs. It&#8217;s better for Clear Street, obviously, but they believ=
e that it&#8217;s also better for those clients from a risk, financing, and=
 speed perspective.&#160;</p><div class=3D"captioned-image-container-static=
